pubis in males?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Tanner stage 1","Tanner stage 2","Tanner stage 3","Tanner stage 4","Tanner stage 5"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETanner stage 3\u003C/strong\u003E in males is characterised by continued penile enlargement (especially in length), initial scrotal enlargement, and darker, coarser pubic hair that begins to curl and spread sparsely over the pubis. Peak height velocity and spermarche typically occur during this stage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETanner stage 1\u003C/strong\u003E represents the prepubertal state with no visible pubertal changes. \u003Cstrong\u003ETanner stage 2\u003C/strong\u003E shows initial scrotal and testicular growth with sparse, straight pubic hair. \u003Cstrong\u003ETanner stage 4\u003C/strong\u003E demonstrates adult-type pubic hair that has not spread to the medial thighs. \u003Cstrong\u003ETanner stage 5\u003C/strong\u003E represents full maturity with adult genitalia and pubic hair distribution.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Tanner stage 3 in males is characterised by continued penile growth, initial scrotal enlargement, and darker/coarser pubic hair.","Peak height velocity and spermarche typically occur during Tanner stage 3 in males.","The Tanner staging system describes physical development through puberty using separate criteria for genitalia and pubic hair."],"references":["Miller BS, Sarafoglou K, Addo OY. Development of Tanner Stage-Age Adjusted CDC Height Curves for Research and Clinical Applications. J Endocr Soc. 2020 Jul 17;4(9):bvaa098. doi: 10.1210/jendso/bvaa098. PMID: 32818164; PMCID: PMC7426000.","Emmanuel M, Bokor BR. Tanner Stages. [Updated 2022 Dec 11]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470280/","Lissauer, T., \u0026 Carroll, W. (Eds.). (2021). Il